# Multi-Agent Swarm Orchestration

## When to Activate

When the user's message contains any of these trigger phrases, **immediately** read and follow the orchestrator skill at `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md`:

- "编排模式" — general orchestration (feature, refactor, or auto-detect)
- "开发并测试" — develop and test a feature
- "修复并测试" — fix a bug and test the fix
- "编排修复" — orchestrated bug fix
- "全流程" — full pipeline (all agents)
- "测试：" — test only, skip dev agents
- "补充测试" — test only, skip dev agents
- "写测试" — test only, skip dev agents

## Scenario Detection

If the trigger phrase alone does not clarify the scenario, infer from context:

| Signal | Scenario |
|--------|----------|
| Words like "bug", "报错", "失败", "异常", "修复", "fix" | Bug Fix |
| Words like "重构", "refactor", "优化结构" | Refactor |
| Words like "测试：", "补充测试", "写测试", "test only" | **Test Only** (skip dev agents, only run test agent) |
| Everything else (new endpoint, new page, new feature) | New Feature |

## Agent Roster

All agents are **tech-stack agnostic** — they auto-detect the project's languages, frameworks, and conventions before doing any work.

| Agent | Role | Dispatch Timing |
|-------|------|----------------|
| `frontend-agent` | Client-side / UI development | Step 2: 并行开发（按需） |
| `backend-agent` | Server-side / API development | Step 2: 并行开发（按需） |
| `dev-agent` | General-purpose fallback | Step 2: 当前后端无法分离时 |
| `review-agent` | Code quality review（只读） | Step 3: 与 test-agent 并行 |
| `test-agent` | Test writing & execution | Step 3: 与 review-agent 并行 |
| `doc-agent` | Documentation generation | Step 5: 最后执行 |

## Mandatory First Step: Tech Stack Detection

The orchestrator MUST auto-detect the project's tech stack before dispatching any agent. This includes:
- Languages and frameworks (frontend + backend)
- Test frameworks per module
- Package manager
- Monorepo structure (if applicable)
- Immutable files (database schemas, API contracts, generated code)
- Code style configuration

This **Project Context** is passed to every subagent.

## Behavior Constraints

### Frontend Agent Boundaries
- Auto-detects frontend framework (React, Vue, Angular, Svelte, etc.)
- CAN modify: client-side code, UI components, styles, i18n, state management
- MUST NOT modify: server-side code, test files, immutable files

### Backend Agent Boundaries
- Auto-detects backend framework (NestJS, Spring, Django, FastAPI, Go, etc.)
- CAN modify: server-side code, API endpoints, services, data access
- MUST NOT modify: client-side code, test files, database schemas (unless explicitly required), immutable files

### Dev Agent Boundaries (fallback)
- Used when frontend/backend split is unclear
- CAN modify: any non-test code
- MUST NOT modify: test files, immutable files

### Test Agent Boundaries
- Auto-detects test framework (Jest, Vitest, pytest, JUnit, Go test, etc.)
- MUST NOT modify business code (anything outside test files)
- MUST run tests after writing them and report results

### Review Agent Boundaries
- Read-only — MUST NOT modify any files
- Reviews against the project's own standards (auto-detected)

### Doc Agent Boundaries
- CAN create/modify: documentation files only
- MUST NOT modify any code or test files

### Orchestrator Responsibilities
- Auto-detect project tech stack before dispatching (Step 0)
- Analyze and decompose the user's requirement
- Determine which agents to activate based on requirement + tech stack
- Dispatch frontend and backend agents **in parallel** when both are needed
- Dispatch review and test agents **in parallel** after dev work completes
- Pass complete context (including Project Context) to each subagent
- Handle failures with auto-retry (max 2 cycles)
- Dispatch doc agent after all dev/review/test work is done
- Produce a final Swarm summary report for the user
